Yes, but only after the GOP's plummeting poll numbers and Clinton's re-election forced Republicans to abandon the harder edges of their agenda. And, oh yeah, the Clinton economic boom (which occurred in the face of countless Republican predictions that his tax increases would wreck the economy) made the whole process much easier.
